<TITLE> Moeen's resignation accepted </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 9 (bdnews24.com)  The resignation of Bangladesh Olympic Association president and former army chief General Moeen U Ahmed was accepted on Thursday. "The meeting unanimously accepted the resignation of the outgoing president and decided to hold another meeting in the next week to process the election procedure as the constitution has no provision of appointing an acting president among the existing vice-presidents," said BOA secretary general Kutubuddin Ahmed after the meeting. Moeen tendered his resignation on Tuesday, over two-and-a-half years before his four-year stint expired. Except one year in 1991 during the BNP government, the Army Chief has been appointed or elected the BOA president since it was formed in 1977. And from then, the Army Chief traditionally steps down from the BOA top post following his retirement and the new army chief takes over. But this time, there is a whisper in the sports arena that the government might like to see a civilian at the top. bd
